webpackJsonp([0x70cc1d038127],{329:function(A,a){A.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/tech-84f598a3896d271a6bdbaab95494ff67-ab4eb.jpg"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 1080px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 66.54713114754098%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/jpeg;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Tools"\n        title="Taken from my Instagram"\n        src="/static/tech-84f598a3896d271a6bdbaab95494ff67-5025c.jpg"\n        srcset="/static/tech-84f598a3896d271a6bdbaab95494ff67-097a5.jpg 270w,\n/static/tech-84f598a3896d271a6bdbaab95494ff67-d02ea.jpg 540w,\n/static/tech-84f598a3896d271a6bdbaab95494ff67-5025c.jpg 1080w,\n/static/tech-84f598a3896d271a6bdbaab95494ff67-66465.jpg 1620w,\n/static/tech-84f598a3896d271a6bdbaab95494ff67-ab4eb.jpg 1952w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>TL;DR I use Javascript for everything :D</p>\n<p>So I thought about sharing the tools I personally use personally or at work, so let’s start with the design tools:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Adobe Illustrator for logos, icons, illustrations.</li>\n<li>Adobe XD or Invision Studio for designing user interfaces &#x26; wireframes.</li>\n<li>Adobe Photoshop for editing pictures &#x26; memes :D</li>\n<li>Adobe After effects for editing videos (I recommend Adobe Premiere Pro for editing videos &#x26; AE to add effects).</li>\n<li>Dribble for inspiration and I share my work there as well as on Behance</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Let’s now get into the tools I use while coding:</p>\n<p>I share my code &#x26; look for inspirations on:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Github</li>\n<li>Codepen</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If I’m simply coding an interface that I’ll might integrate into an app (web or native) I use plain html/css &#x26; vanilla js.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Jekyll or Gatsby (I recommend Gatsby), I use Github to host the files and I deploy on Netlify.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For Css I’m cool to use what ever tech available out there that makes my task done quickly &#x26; well, I have personally used Bootstrap 3 &#x26; 4, Bulma, Lostgrid, Materliaze, Tachyons &#x26; made my own little framework called Unnamed that has over 175 stars on Github, but I seriously prefer using cssGrid &#x26; I always enjoy styling my elements from scratch since the components are fully reusable with react.</p>\n<p>If I’m making a web app, for the front end I use the <code class="language-text">create-react-app</code> boilerplate as it’s the official one from the team that made React Js but I always have to add react-router, Redux, Recompose &#x26; many other modules I use the most.</p>\n<p>I obviously use Git bash as my terminal when I’m on windows but I go with iTerm2 when I’m on macOS &#x26; VScode as my code editor (material theme).</p>\n<p>For the backend, I was using php/mysql but I didn’t personally like it and switched to node js and so I currently use Express Js/Mongoose and Mongodb as database to make Restful APIs which I deploy on Heroku.</p>\n<p>Forgot to mention that I sometimes use Firebase when I’m too lazy to work on the backend.</p>\n<p>For native apps, I use React native to build mobile apps (Ios &#x26; Android).</p>\n<p>For growth hacking, I focus more on building useful products that users really need in their lives then I simply share it on Product Hunt, Hacker news, Reddit and on social media.</p>\n<p>I use Windows 10, MacOs Mojave, my MSI GP62 laptop, my macbook pro 2017 touchbar work laptop, Nexus 6p with a Dbrand wood skin. Full setup can be found <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1falYEEHhJxq4HIXwOPoc4lk0AYsfHY4U6ZCcY4Srs8g/edit?usp=sharing">here</a>.</p>',timeToRead:2,frontmatter:{date:"February 27, 2018",edited:"July 08, 2018",path:"/the-tech-tools-I-use",title:"The tech tools I use",next:"/istanbul-trip",id:9,thumbnail:{childImageSharp:{sizes:{base64:"data:image/jpeg;base64,",aspectRatio:1.5026943802925328,src:"/static/tech-84f598a3896d271a6bdbaab95494ff67-f2ac0.jpg",srcSet:"/static/tech-84f598a3896d271a6bdbaab95494ff67-567e3.jpg 158w,\n/static/tech-84f598a3896d271a6bdbaab95494ff67-c3206.jpg 315w,\n/static/tech-84f598a3896d271a6bdbaab95494ff67-f2ac0.jpg 630w,\n/static/tech-84f598a3896d271a6bdbaab95494ff67-0c4a5.jpg 945w,\n/static/tech-84f598a3896d271a6bdbaab95494ff67-211f3.jpg 1260w,\n/static/tech-84f598a3896d271a6bdbaab95494ff67-0150a.jpg 1890w,\n/static/tech-84f598a3896d271a6bdbaab95494ff67-c287a.jpg 1952w",sizes:"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px"}}}}}},pathContext:{}}}});
